Being about 50m from the street, the privacy of the house and the yard, the peace and fresh air are exactly what is needed for a total disconnection from the noise and hustle and bustle of everyday life. The hammock and swings in the yard - priceless. The stew in the cauldron, the barbecue, the large terrace (perfect for board games), the very nicely decorated rooms and equipped with absolutely everything you need - are just a few of the arguments for returning here with great pleasure.

title: Her (Chalet) is wonderful in the picturesque village of Comarnic
positiveReview: This is a family chalet with a living room, a fully equipped kitchen, and 3 bedrooms, providing a fun home comfort experience. The place is spacious and clean. The house is built on a slope and there is a balcony with outdoor furniture, overlooking a large green and shady yard with children's facilities and a swing bench, a grilling facility, and more. The host was attentive to all our requests and answered our questions about places to hang out, walk, and shop.
negativeReview: Accessibility: It is not possible to park close to the house and there is a stepped access path about forty meters long, from the street down the yard to the house, which may be a bit challenging or even impossible for those with limited mobility. This information was provided in advance, but only after the reservation was made.
